Solve Barrier: To overcome this barrier, it may be helpful to provide resources and information on local food assistance programs, farmer's markets, or community gardens that offer affordable and fresh produce. Additionally, discussing alternative options such as meal delivery services or online grocery shopping can help ensure he has access to nutritious food choices.

Educate: Educate the patient on the importance of dietary management in heart failure, emphasizing the impact of food choices on his condition and overall health. Encourage him to prioritize his nutrition and offer support in finding convenient and accessible ways to maintain a healthy diet despite potential challenges in his neighborhood.